2dea6d81-4358-416f-ac5d-2cdb3429dfdc	a8df0e57-aaac-4a60-ba5d-91aa239c6233	Rosa Luxemburg Stiftung Scholarship 2027 in Germany	Germany	masters	full	1 October 2026	https://www.rosalux.de/en/foundation/studienwerk/scholarships	The Rosa Luxemburg Stiftung (RLS) offers scholarships for Master's and PhD students from all countries. The scholarship covers a monthly stipend, academic and research support, seminars, workshops, training, and mentorship from experienced researchers. The application round for 2027 begins in mid-August 2025, with a deadline of 1 October 2026. Preference is given to women, those in social need, and people with disabilities. Students in STEM and public administration are especially encouraged to apply.	Open to students of all nationalities pursuing a Master's degree in any field. Preference is given to women, individuals with social need, and those with disabilities. Strong applications from STEM and public administration are especially encouraged. No specific CGPA requirement is mentioned.	Medium	• Clearly articulate your commitment to social justice and left-wing political values in your application.\n• Highlight any involvement in community service, activism, or political engagement.\n• Prepare a strong academic project plan or research proposal that aligns with the foundation's mission.\n• Submit all documents early and ensure completeness before the 1 October 2026 deadline.\n• If applicable, emphasize your background in STEM or public administration to stand out.	{Germany,Masters,"Full Funding",International,"STEM Encouraged","Public Administration","Social Justice",Left-Wing}	The Rosa Luxemburg Stiftung Scholarship 2027 is a fully funded opportunity for Master's students from any country to study in Germany. Offered by a political foundation rooted in socialist values, this scholarship provides a monthly stipend, academic support, workshops, seminars, and mentorship from experienced researchers. It is ideal for Bangladeshi students who are passionate about social justice, political change, and community engagement. The foundation particularly encourages applications from women, those in social need, people with disabilities, and students in STEM or public administration. With no specific CGPA requirement, the selection focuses on academic promise and commitment to progressive ideals. Studying in Germany under this scholarship not only covers living expenses but also offers a vibrant intellectual environment through networking events and training programs.	A photorealistic image of the historic main building of Humboldt University in Berlin at golden hour, with warm sunlight casting long shadows. The sky has a soft gradient of orange and red, reflecting the foundation's socialist ideals. The architecture is neoclassical with columns and a grand entrance. The mood is intellectual and aspirational, with a calm, focused atmosphere. No text or people are present. Colors: deep reds, golds, and warm earth tones.	https://gmhowygqtvfuftumkbzp.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/scholarship-thumbnails/2dea6d81-4358-416f-ac5d-2cdb3429dfdc/thumbnail.webp	published	2026-06-12 14:28:02.54392+00	2026-06-12 14:28:41.701311+00	f
a12af600-2188-4631-adc1-251852141aff	a8df0e57-aaac-4a60-ba5d-91aa239c6233	Sapienza University Scholarships 2026 in Italy	Italy	any	other	Rolling	https://www.uniroma1.it/en/pagina/scholarships	Sapienza University of Rome offers a variety of scholarships for Bachelor's, Master's, and PhD students. Funding types vary by program and may include full or partial tuition fee waivers, living allowances, free or discounted accommodation through LazioDiSco housing, research and thesis support, and access to university facilities such as libraries, labs, and career services. Specific scholarships include those for students with care responsibilities or in vulnerable circumstances, reimbursement for psychological counselling, study materials, accommodation, regional scholarships (Disco Lazio), grants for rental and healthcare costs, scholarships for the Rieti campus, the 'Wanted the Best' scholarship for meritorious students, international thesis scholarships, international post-degree scholarships (monthly amount €1,290 for internships), scholarships for study and training abroad (including Erasmus+), grants from the Italian government, the #100ragazzeSTEM scholarship for women in STEM, student-collaboration scholarships (paid internships of 150 hours, €1,295 or €1,500 for disability support), thesis awards, and scholarships for specialisation schools. Deadlines vary by program and are not specified on the main page.	Eligibility varies by program, but generally open to international students (including Bangladeshi) applying for Bachelor's, Master's, or PhD programs at Sapienza University. Some scholarships require high academic merit (e.g., 'Wanted the Best' for top students), while others target specific groups like women in STEM, students with care responsibilities, or those in vulnerable circumstances. No fixed CGPA cutoff is specified, but competitive awards often demand strong transcripts.	Medium	• Carefully read the specific eligibility criteria for each scholarship program (e.g., #100ragazzeSTEM, Disco Lazio, or thesis awards).\n• Prepare all documents early: academic transcripts, motivation letter, recommendation letters, and proof of language proficiency (Italian or English as required).\n• Apply as early as possible since deadlines are rolling and many funds are limited.\n• For accommodation and living cost support, check the LazioDiSco regional scholarship requirements separately.\n• Explore merit-based and need-based options together—some scholarships can be stacked if eligibility permits.	{Italy,"Sapienza University",Rome,Bachelor's,Master's,PhD,"Tuition Waiver","Women in STEM"}	Sapienza University of Rome, one of Europe's oldest and most prestigious universities, offers a wide array of scholarships for international students, including Bangladeshis, in 2026. From full tuition waivers and living allowances to housing support through LazioDiSco, these opportunities cover almost every need. Whether you're pursuing a Bachelor's, Master's, or PhD, you can find funding that matches your profile—be it a merit-based award like 'Wanted the Best,' a regional grant for housing and healthcare, or the #100ragazzeSTEM scholarship encouraging women in STEM. The rolling deadlines mean you should start your application early, but the flexibility allows you to apply at any time. With additional support for student collaborations, thesis research, and even internships abroad, Sapienza is an excellent choice for Bangladeshi students seeking a world-class education in the heart of Rome.	A photorealistic image of the main entrance of Sapienza University of Rome at golden hour, with warm sunlight casting long shadows on the classical stone columns and arches. The sky is a mix of soft orange and pale blue, with a few wispy clouds. In the foreground, a cobblestone path leads to the grand doorway, flanked by lush green hedges. The mood is prestigious and welcoming, with deep gold and terracotta tones reflecting the university's history and prestige. No people or text visible.	https://gmhowygqtvfuftumkbzp.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/scholarship-thumbnails/a12af600-2188-4631-adc1-251852141aff/thumbnail.webp	published	2026-06-12 14:30:51.261053+00	2026-06-12 14:32:08.537004+00	f
