bd9fbe02-8811-40d1-b1bf-7f0d54cabc9d	Scholarship 2027 is a fully funded opportunity for Master's students from any country to study in Germany. Offered by a political foundation rooted in socialist values, this scholarship provides a monthly stipend, academic support, workshops, seminars, and mentorship from experienced researchers. It is ideal for Bangladeshi students who are passionate about social justice, political change, and community engagement. The foundation particularly encourages applications from women, those in social need, people with disabilities, and students in STEM or public administration. With no specific CGPA requirement, the selection focuses on academic promise and commitment to progressive ideals. Studying in Germany under this scholarship not only covers living expenses but also offers a vibrant intellectual environment through networking events and training programs.\n\nEligibility:\nOpen to students	{"index": 1, "title": "Rosa Luxemburg Stiftung Scholarship 2027 in Germany", "country": "Germany"}	[-0.01763916,-0.052520752,0.016433716,0.03086853,0.017944336,0.008483887,-0.017059326,-0.020812988,-0.021118164,-0.04397583,0.007598877,-0.020019531,-0.028579712,-0.024810791,0.020523071,0.0015001297,0.040374756,-0.009033203,-0.10046387,0.051696777,-0.0052261353,0.009216309,-0.004386902,0.034454346,0.034729004,-0.020904541,-0.046142578,0.029785156,-0.020339966,0.066101074,0.032958984,-0.0017337799,-0.0012683868,-0.030563354,-0.03555298,0.007598877,-0.035308838,0.0032691956,-0.0073661804,0.03466797,0.028625488,-0.020828247,0.064331055,0.04244995,0.0022563934,0.0063171387,0.039916992,-0.0042877197,0.041534424,0.00844574,-0.03262329,0.0234375,-0.021560669,-0.03363037,-0.030563354,-0.029907227,0.03237915,0.024551392,0.029632568,0.027694702,0.08758545,0.02180481,0.041503906,-0.019805908,-0.036987305,0.025527954,-0.00057315826,0.046539307,0.029785156,0.02696228,0.0016345978,0.003572464,0.01876831,-0.02822876,0.052520752,0.008094788,-0.046569824,-0.00531