f9282e94-65b5-4f2c-ac70-3bd549a0ce98	7eb77cca3a9addb759d4f6718940ca576a26aaebf7cb9b6d73aed6659cc3d741	deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash	What is Chevening?	**Chevening** is the UK government's global scholarship programme, funded by the Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) and partner organisations. It's designed to develop future leaders by offering full financial support for a one-year master's degree at any UK university.\n\n**Who is it for?**\n- Bangladeshi students (and citizens of other eligible countries) with a strong academic background and leadership potential.\n\n**What does it cover?**\n- Full tuition fees (any UK university, any eligible master's course)\n- Monthly living allowance (stipend)\n- Return economy airfare to the UK\n- Arrival allowance, visa fees, and a thesis/departure allowance\n- Exclusive networking events and access to the global Chevening alumni community\n\n**Key Requirements (2024/25 cycle):**\n- A bachelor's degree (minimum 2:1 or equivalent; for 3-year Bangladeshi degrees, you usually need a strong result)\n- At least **2 years of work experience** (full-time, part-time, paid, or voluntary – internships can count, but careful calculation is needed)\n- Proficiency in English (IELTS/PTE/TOEFL can be accepted, but Chevening itself does not require it at application stage; the university will set the requirements)\n- Strong leadership and networking skills (demonstrable through extracurriculars, volunteering, or professional achievements)\n\n**Application Timeline (Typical for Bangladesh):**\n- Applications open: August/September\n- Deadline: early November\n- Interviews: January–March (shortlisted candidates are invited for an interview at the British High Commission in Dhaka)\n- Results: June–August\n\n**Practical Tip:** Chevening is **not a CGPA-only scholarship** – it heavily weighs your leadership potential, networking ability, and clear career plan. A strong SOP and interview performance can outweigh a slightly lower CGPA.\n