83047f5d-aa19-468f-a82c-398f4169cf5f	82117f0e7001c89df7c1e006d1e4dd39d466292da6236e9caee61f3ddfcb1cca	deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash	Create a 90-day prep plan	Here’s a **90-day prep plan** for a Bangladeshi student targeting **Fall 2025 / Spring 2026** admissions and major scholarships (DAAD, Erasmus, Commonwealth, Fulbright, etc.).\n\nUse this as a checklist. Adjust days based on your current progress.\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Days 1–30: Foundation & Research\n\n### Week 1–2: Goal Setting & Test Registration\n- [ ] Decide 2–3 countries (Germany, UK, Canada, Australia, US, Netherlands)\n- [ ] List **10–15 universities** + specific programs (check deadlines: Oct–Mar for most)\n- [ ] Register for **IELTS / TOEFL / Duolingo** (book within 45 days)\n- [ ] If needed: **GRE / GMAT** – register if program requires it\n\n### Week 3–4: Deep Research & Document Collection\n- [ ] Gather: all transcripts (SSC/HSC/Bachelor), mark sheets, certificates\n- [ ] Request **WES / ICAS** evaluation (if applying to North America)\n- [ ] Note scholarship deadlines:\n  - **DAAD** (for Germany): typically July–September\n  - **Erasmus Mundus**: October–January\n  - **Commonwealth Shared**: November–December\n  - **Chevening**: September–November\n  - **Fulbright**: April–June (for next cycle)\n- [ ] Build a spreadsheet: program, deadline, requirements, fees, scholarship link\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Days 31–60: Application Materials\n\n### Week 5–6: Test Prep & Early Drafts\n- [ ] Take mock tests weekly (IELTS/GRE)\n- [ ] Write **first drafts of SOP** (tailored to 2–3 programs for now)\n- [ ] Make **CV/Resume** (max 2 pages, academic + work/volunteer)\n- [ ] Contact 2–3 professors/supervisors for **recommendation letters** (give them 3 weeks)\n\n### Week 7–8: Polish & Refine\n- [ ] Finalize test date (aim for IELTS band 7+ / TOEFL 95+)\n- [ ] **Revise SOP** → customise for each university (why this program, why you)\n- [ ] Prepare statement of research interest (if applying for research-based programs)\n- [ ] Confirm recommendation letters are uploaded or signed\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Days 61–90: Submit & Prepare\n\n### Week 9–10: Applications Open\n- [ ] **Submit first 3 applications** (early deadlines, Erasmus/UK)\n- [ ] Upload transcripts, CV, LORs, SOP, test scores\n- [ ] Double-check each portal: no missing fields, correct documents\n- [ ] Pay application fees or request fee waivers\n\n### Week 11–12: Final	1	2026-06-10 05:17:23.064962+00	2026-06-10 16:36:40.423144+00	2026-06-11 05:17:22.908+00
